**Architecture decisions:**
- Toast system subscribes to the existing `MESSAGE` event bus rather than new event types — all high-importance messages already go through `addMessage()` with typed categories, so filtering by type is a clean zero-coupling approach.
- `showToast()` is exported for potential future callers (e.g., game-over panel) but initToasts() self-wires all subscriptions — consumers don't need to wire anything themselves.
- Summary panel reads `empireos-achievements` localStorage directly (same pattern as settingsPanel.js) to avoid importing achievements.js (which registers event listeners and could cause duplicate subscriptions if imported multiple times).
- `_tickCountdown()` handler checks panel visibility before re-rendering — avoids wasted renders when the panel is hidden (e.g., user is on Buildings tab). This is the first panel to use this pattern.
- Victory condition thresholds are local constants mirroring systems/victory.js — no import needed and no tight coupling to the victory system.

